
[1]serviceableness

   SERV'ICEABLENESS, n.

   1. Usefulness of promoting good of any kind; beneficialness.

   All action being for some end, its aptness to be commanded or forbidden
   must be founded upon its serviceableness or disserviceableness to some
   end. Norris.

   2. Officiousness; readiness to do service.
